Maternity Leave Policies: Trade-Offs Between Labour Market Demands and Health 
Benefits for Children.

Strang L, Broeks M.

Comment in
    For more information, see 
https://www.rand.org/pubs/research_reports/RR1734.html.

Over recent years many European Union countries have made changes to the design 
of the maternity leave provision. These policy developments reflect calls for 
greater gender equality in the workforce and more equal share of childcare 
responsibilities. However, while research shows that long period of leave can 
have negative effects on women's labour market attachment and career 
